Claiming Price $20,000 (Races Where Entered For $15,000 Or Less Not Consi dered In Allowances). Oklahoma Bred Claiming Price $25,000. (If management deems it necessary to take this race off the Turf, it will be run at a distance of 1 Mile on the main track.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DON'TASK DON'TTELL was settled while inside on the backstretch, rallied on the far turn, moved out to be three wide in upper stretch for clear running room then quickly drew away in late stretch to be much the best. TEO stalked the pace while inside on the backstretch, saved ground on the far turn then rallied and slipped through to be second best in the end. BOX SEAT was unhurried early and inside on the backstretch, rallied and made a bid, moved out to be four wide in mid stretch but was out finished for the place. ENGLANDER was unhurried early then rallied on the far turn while two wide, was making a run then forced out and placed in tight in mid stretch and was no menace in the end. ROYALLY was unhurried early while inside, rallied and moved out to be seven wide in upper stretch and closed willingly in late stretch. TED was allowed to settled while two wide, made a bid three wide on the far turn to mid stretch then flattened out in late stretch. MACEDONIAN RULER (AUS) was unhurried early then raced four wide on the far turn, moved out to be eight wide in upper stretch and was no threat. JOHAN ZOFFANI (IRE) was unhurried early on then rallied on the far turn while three wide, moved out to be five wide in upper stretch and was no threat. SAINT CHARLES set a pressured pace from the start and inside into the far turn, was in a long drive but gave way in the stretch. EASTER SNAP sat back at the start and spotted the field many lengths, was settled then outrun. HAP HOT chased the early pace while two wide on the backstretch, was used up then stopped. A claim of foul was lodged by the rider of ENGLANDER against the rider of BOX SEAT for interference in mid stretch. After reviewing the film's, no action was taken.
